VRChat occasionally adds new enum values (e.g. a new GroupPermissions entry
like "group-instance-bypass-avatar-performance") in between client
regenerations. The generator emits a hardcoded AllowedXxxEnumValues list and
an UnmarshalJSON that errors if the incoming value isn't on it, which makes
the entire containing object — and any list it's part of — fail to decode
over a single unknown enum value.

Replace each enum's UnmarshalJSON body with a relaxed version that just casts
the incoming string and returns nil:

	func (v *T) UnmarshalJSON(src []byte) error {
		var value string
		err := json.Unmarshal(src, &value)
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		*v = T(value)
		return nil
	}

Leave IsValid() and NewTFromValue strict — callers who explicitly want
allowlist validation still have it.
